The Impact of Obesity on Microglial Function: Immune, Metabolic and Endocrine 
Perspectives.

Alexaki VI(1).

Author information:
(1)Institute for Clinical Chemistry and Laboratory Medicine, University Clinic 
Carl Gustav Carus, TU Dresden, Fetscherstrasse 74, 01307 Dresden, Germany.

Increased life expectancy in combination with modern life style and high 
prevalence of obesity are important risk factors for development of 
neurodegenerative diseases. Neuroinflammation is a feature of neurodegenerative 
diseases, and microglia, the innate immune cells of the brain, are central 
players in it. The present review discusses the effects of obesity, chronic 
peripheral inflammation and obesity-associated metabolic and endocrine 
perturbations, including insulin resistance, dyslipidemia and increased 
glucocorticoid levels, on microglial function.

